# canonical_chapters.txt — OPTIONAL chapter-order override
#
# By default, scripts/compile.sh concatenates chapters by filename sort.
# That works if your files follow the 01_xxx.md, 02_xxx.md, 10_xxx.md convention.
#
# Rename this file to canonical_chapters.txt (remove .example) ONLY if:
#   - You want to omit certain chapters from a build (e.g. unfinished drafts)
#   - Your filenames don't sort cleanly
#   - You want to build an Act 1 or sample compile with a subset
#
# One chapter filename per line, relative to manuscript/chapters/.
# Lines starting with # are ignored. Blank lines are ignored.
#
# Example:
# 01_the_oracle.md
# 02_the_inquisitor.md
# 03_first_meeting.md
